**\\n\\nIt looks like I'm considering a library class related to image metadata. I wonder if the native image metadata includes the class, or if it might actually avoid compile-time references. I'm thinking about dynamic class loading and how to handle that without strictly targeting a specific call site. Maybe adding a test to resolve a rest-assured class by name without referencing the target type could be a good approach!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_dclDICb6lMRgOUjRdEjX0V18|fc_0583b49b15aeb7a9016a00a56543b4819080310ce955a6a807", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/main/extracted/io/restassured/internal/http/BasicNameValuePairWithNoValueSupport.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 22186, "output": 1707, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48469, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778427205605, "responseId": "resp_0583b49b15aeb7a9016a00a54726608190bf429d0a54b15486"}}
